  "content": [
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "text": "Charles Bronson, whose name at birth was Charles Buchinsky, was born and raised in Ehrenfeld, Pennsylvania. He died of pneumonia in 2003, at the age of 81."
    },
    {
      "type": "break"
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.searchdictionaries.com/?q=charles+bronson+(actor)",
      "sourceTitle": "Who is Charles Bronson (actor)?",
      "text": "It doesn't appear that Bronson talked about religion much in his life. The unsourced speculation around the internet claims he was either Lutheran"
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "sourceUrl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Eastern_Orthodox_Christians",
      "sourceTitle": "List of Eastern Orthodox Christians.",
      "text": "or Eastern Orthodox,"
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "sourceUrl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Eastern_Orthodox_Christians",
      "sourceTitle": "List of Eastern Orthodox Christians.",
      "text": "and possibly Russian Orthodox at some point in his life."
    },
    {
      "type": "break"
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "sourceUrl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Religion_in_Lithuania#Lutheranism",
      "sourceTitle": "Religion in Lithuania.",
      "text": "Both of his parents were Lithuanian, where the vast majority are Catholic,"
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "sourceUrl": "http://ethnicelebs.com/charles-bronson",
      "sourceTitle": "Charles Bronson.",
      "text": "so you would think if it was just blind speculation, that's where people would have jumped. However, it appears that his father was Lithuanian Tatar,"
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "sourceUrl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lithuanian_Tatars#Muslim_Lipka_Tartar_cemetery_in_Bohoniki.2C_Poland_gallery",
      "sourceTitle": "Lipka Tatars.",
      "text": "which are a predominantly Muslim group."
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "sourceUrl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Eastern_Orthodox_Christians",
      "sourceTitle": "List of Eastern Orthodox Christians.",
      "text": "But then there's one site that claims his father was a Kryashen,"
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "sourceUrl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kryashen",
      "sourceTitle": "Kryashens.",
      "text": "or Christianized Tatar, who generally practice Orthodox Christianity."
    },
    {
      "type": "break"
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "text": "Confused yet? I suppose what I'm trying to get to here is that it seems probable that he was raised Eastern Orthodox. But most likely he wasn't very religious during his life or we'd have more than gross speculation."
    },
    {
      "type": "break"
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "sourceUrl": "http://wikibin.org/articles/list-of-hollywood-republicans.html",
      "sourceTitle": "List of Hollywood Republicans.",
      "text": "It doesn't appear that he was very interested in politics either. One website lists him as \"possibly\" a Republican, but without a source I'm going to have to assume they just made that up because it sounded good."
    },
    {
      "type": "break"
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.respectance.com/charles_bronson/",
      "sourceTitle": "Charles Bronson Online Tribute and Memorial Website.",
      "text": "Back in the McCarthy era when Hollywood stars were being blacklisted for sneezing into the wrong colored tissue paper, Bronson changed his name from Buchinsky out of fear that a Russian-sounding name might make him a target."
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "text": "It seems to me that if he were a passionately political man, he might not have tried to fly under the radar."
    },
    {
      "type": "break"
    },
    {
      "type": "sentence",
      "text": "If you have any more information about Bronson, please let us know in the comments."
    },
    {
      "type": "break"
    }
  ],
